This paper discusses the optimal strategies for an attacker to spread malware while maintaining stealth, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses mathematical models to analyze the spread of malware, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of computational policies, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
